ca.uqac.lif.labpal

Class LabAssistant

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.labpal.LabAssistant
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LinearAssistant

    public abstract class LabAssistant
extends Object
implements Runnable
    A lab assistant is in charge of running a set of experiments according to a queue.

    Typically, you add new experiments with queue(Experiment) and remove them from the queue with unqueue(Experiment). You can instruct the lab assistant to start running the experiments in its queue with Runnable.run(), and can interrupt its operation with stop(). Calling clear() will clear the current queue.

    Author:
    Sylvain Hallé
